<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The -TION suffix is the most common word ending in the English language, and it's equally dominant in Scrabble. With over 1,000 valid -TION words in SOWPODS, this noun-forming suffix converts verbs into nouns (act→action, create→creation) using four of the most abundant tiles in the bag. It's your most reliable path to consistent bingos.</p>

<p>The genius of -TION is that all four tiles (T, I, O, N) have 6+ copies in the bag, meaning you'll hold this suffix ready-to-fire more often than any other.</p>

<p>Competitive players treat -TION as the foundation of their bingo strategy — it's the suffix they look for first when scanning their rack.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why -TION Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">T(1)+I(1)+O(1)+N(1) base</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1,000+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid -TION words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6–15</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter length range</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>While the individual tile values are low, -TION's power comes from probability. With 6 T's, 9 I's, 8 O's, and 6 N's in a standard bag, you'll statistically hold at least 3 of the 4 -TION tiles in most racks. This makes -TION bingos far more achievable than high-value suffixes like -IZE.</p>

