<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">TION as a bingo stem:</span> When you see T, I, O, N on your rack, mentally set them aside as your suffix and focus on the remaining 3 tiles as your root. Even common letters like STA+TION, CRE+ATION, or FUN+CTION produce valid bingos.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUESTION — the Q without U word:</span> QUESTION is one of the most valuable -TION words because it uses Q without needing a U tile. At 17 points before premium squares, it's a natural bingo that catches opponents off guard.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hook with S for TIONS:</span> Most -TION words can take an S to become TIONS. This means you can play NATION and later hook an S for NATIONS, or play CREATION knowing someone will S-hook it — but that's free points from the parallel word formed.</p>
